This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it deals with alias resolution techniques that rely on active measurement of IP addresses belonging to a common router. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it discusses the robustness of router signatures and the feasibility and accuracy of the proposed tool. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning classifiers, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of loss traces and the dataset collection could also suggest the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the paper's focus on a new tool and its potential impact on existing techniques could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
